'''''Star Wars Weekly'' 8''' is the eighth issue in the ''[[Star Wars Weekly]]'' series of comic reprints, published on [[March 29]], [[1978]].

==Contents==
*[[Star Wars (1977) 4|''Star Wars'' (1977) 4]] {{C|Part 2}}
*"[[w:c:marvel:Marvel Preview Vol 1 1|Man-Gods from Beyond the Stars]]" {{C|Part 3}}
*"[[w:c:marvel:Marvel Preview Vol 1 4|The Sword in the Star!: Stave 1: Alas, the Seeds of Man!]]" {{C|Part 4}}

*"Spacemail Depot Sector 3" {{C|letters column}}
*"Why Kenny Baker Nearly Shunned ''Star Wars''!" - An interview with [[Kenny Baker]], the operator of the [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] prop, conducted by Audrey Smith.
*A "Pick Your Own Prize" competition, where ten winners can choose from a set of ''Star Wars'' miniature figures; ''Star Wars'' Dip Dots and poster painting set; a ''Star Wars'' Play Doh and paints set; or two ''Star Wars'' keel kites and a set of five ''Star Wars'' masks. All prizes were provided by [[Palitoy]]. To enter, readers must answer six simple ''Star Wars'' related multiple-choice questions.

